The Old Men of The North and South Poles

description: Love. Hate. Fear. Fate. Four words that define our lives in different ways. Four words that lie at the heart of all our experiences. Four words that have long inspired artists to craft their most resonant work. Four-Letter Worlds examines how these four little words define our individual worlds in very big ways. This brand-new anthology features 16 original short stories by 26 renowned creators, including Joe Casey, Chynna Clugston-Major, Antony Johnston, Phil Hester, Jim Mahfood, Scott Morse, and Andi Watson.
name: Love Hate Fear Fate

description:
By May, 1945, the Second World War in Europe was drawing to a close. The Allies were in control and the Germans were surrendering in droves.
But one renegade unit of Ukrainians had fought for the Nazis and knew they could expect no mercy . So they set about stirring up trouble between the Americans and Russians. Suddenly Allied tanks were firing at each other - it looked like the start of World War Three!
name: To the Bitter End

description:
It was an ancient Viking shield and it should have had no place in a twentieth-century war fought with tank and guns. But this shield cast a long shadow.
Oli Jonsen, a Norwegian fighting on the German side, found his loyalties challenged when his unit was sent to recover the shield of his ancesteors from the Russians. Fpr jpw could he allow it to be used to boost Nazi propaganda when he himself as beginning to doubt his masters.
name: The Viking Shield
